73
00:06:18,150 --> 00:06:20,860
I kissed you at the bar that night.

74
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,450
What for?

75
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,540
For you to get over me.

76
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:33,860
But it's like I was running away from myself.

77
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:37,160
I tried to do the bad shit like I used to,

78
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:39,740
fooling around with some girl.

79
00:06:39,740 --> 00:06:42,340
But I ended up thinking of you.

80
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:48,640
So, I came back to ask you for another chance.

81
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:55,850
But I couldn't tell you directly.

82
00:06:56,870 --> 00:06:59,660
Two told me that you'd moved on.

83
00:07:02,650 --> 00:07:07,350
Yes, I've moved on from you.

84
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:13,980
Stop doing stupid shit.

85
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:18,650
If you hadn't found out that I had feelings for you,

86
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,480
you wouldn't have liked me back.

87
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:29,600
One day I would find out, no matter what,

88
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,000
that I can't go on without you.

89
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:41,750
Can we start over?

90
00:07:48,470 --> 00:07:50,780
I don't want to hurt anymore.

91
00:07:58,259 --> 00:08:02,160
No problem. I'll try to be a better person.

92
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:04,650
I'll wait for that day.

93
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,950
The day you like me again.

94
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:24,660
I'm sorry, Lynn.

95
00:08:24,660 --> 00:08:27,250
There was a commotion earlier.

96
00:08:27,790 --> 00:08:30,300
I'm walking to the car right now.

97
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,100
Okay.

98
00:08:35,610 --> 00:08:38,920
What were you thinking, Un?

99
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:42,290
Why did you go and kiss some random girl?

100
00:08:42,290 --> 00:08:44,680
That's not you.

101
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:47,350
Yeah.

102
00:08:47,350 --> 00:08:49,780
I must have been heartbroken.

103
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:51,379
Heartbroken?

104
00:08:51,379 --> 00:08:52,760
Who?

105
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:56,451
Never mind. That person just became unavailable.

106
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:06,020
Would you like to go out with me?

107
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:22,590
[Cafe Tonchabub]

108
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:36,680
Third, let's grab something to eat.

109
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,120
No, I have to work on the script.

110
00:09:40,810 --> 00:09:45,050
Come on, Third. Don't you have time for me?

111
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:47,480
The opening night is coming soon.

112
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,770
Aren't you working in the sounds unit?

113
00:09:49,770 --> 00:09:52,820
They're complaining that they're working themselves into the ground.

114
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,860
You're not supposed to be available.

115
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:57,700
Now that you're not using crutches anymore, help them out.

116
00:10:02,980 --> 00:10:06,200
Fine, I'll go.

117
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,740
I'm going.

118
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,440
I'm going, Third.

119
00:10:13,470 --> 00:10:15,410
I'm really going.

120
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:17,550
Get gone already!

121
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:19,600
I have to work.

122
00:10:46,710 --> 00:10:48,750
Why are you so mean?

123
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:53,330
Mean? I'm really busy.

124
00:10:53,330 --> 00:10:56,150
Getting something to eat takes a minute. I don't see why it's a problem.

125
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:57,650
That's right.

126
00:10:58,370 --> 00:11:00,350
I don't want to side with him.

127
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:06,260
But Khai went so far as to punch P'Un for you, even though he didn't think it through.

128
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:10,132
But when it comes to you, he doesn't use his brain.

129
00:11:10,132 --> 00:11:13,372
Just cut him some slack.

130
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:24,360
No, I'm not going. I'm busy.

131
00:11:35,870 --> 00:11:37,870
Hey, you're here already.

132
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:40,220
I got here early for nothing.

133
00:11:42,820 --> 00:11:44,450
Aren't you a little too dressed up?

134
00:11:44,450 --> 00:11:47,180
You're not on a date with a girl.

135
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:48,980
I'm on a date.

136
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,310
I got you something.

137
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,860
What is this?

138
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:11,750
Don't you like it?

139
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:14,820
Let's go. I'm hungry.

140
00:12:19,730 --> 00:12:22,240
[Akiyoshi]

141
00:12:32,890 --> 00:12:34,890
That's fine.

142
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:36,610
I'll get it.

143
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:38,350
No, I can just tell the waiter.

144
00:12:38,350 --> 00:12:40,360
I can get it faster.

145
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:48,500
Here you go.

146
00:13:07,322 --> 00:13:09,672
This is mine.

147
00:13:09,672 --> 00:13:13,380
I know. I'm boiling it for you.

148
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:21,500
For a shrimp, you boil it and eat right away.

149
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:24,310
- I'll peel it for you.
- I can do it myself.

150
00:13:24,310 --> 00:13:27,441
It'll hurt your hands. Your hands will be a mess after you're done.

151
00:13:27,441 --> 00:13:29,691
Let me do it.

152
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:34,750
No, it'll be salty from your hands. I don't want to eat that.

153
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:36,460
Salty? I can wash my hands.

154
00:13:36,460 --> 00:13:38,060
Stop!

155
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:42,091
Are you crazy? The water is boiling hot!

156
00:13:43,940 --> 00:13:46,510
I'm peeling it. It only takes a second.

157
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,140
Hello.

158
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:12,350
Dinner? With Bone, too?

159
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,500
I'm busy.

160
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:25,410
Did they ask you to grab something to eat?

161
00:14:25,410 --> 00:14:27,210
Yeah.

162
00:14:27,210 --> 00:14:30,380
Why didn't you ask them to join us?

163
00:14:30,380 --> 00:14:34,400
By the time they get here, our buffet time will be up.

164
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:38,100
We're here! Aren't we fast?

165
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:39,980
How did you get here?

166
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:41,270
Coincidence.

167
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:43,570
We see both Khai and Third together.

168
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:45,630
How is this possible?

169
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,350
You said you were boiling with work piling up.

170
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:53,707
In fact, you came to eat boiling shabu with Khunphol.

171
00:14:53,707 --> 00:14:55,048
It's a coincidence.

172
00:14:55,048 --> 00:14:56,939
If you want to eat, come and have a seat.

173
00:14:56,939 --> 00:15:00,430
No, we don't want to accidentally sit at the same table.

174
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,410
Can we use the one right next to you?

175
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:04,970
It must be reserved for someone.

176
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:06,460
That someone is me.

177
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:07,591
Yes.

178
00:15:07,591 --> 00:15:09,791
How are you that quick?

179
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:36,840
Not so smooth.

180
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:40,160
I saw both of you when you were walking into the restaurant.

181
00:15:45,870 --> 00:15:49,650
How hard is it to peel a shrimp?

182
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:52,220
The chopstick moment was great.

183
00:15:52,830 --> 00:15:56,200
#ThirdNotAGoodLiar

184
00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:07,107
Our cover has been blown. Should we just tell them we're a couple?

185
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:13,650
A couple, my ass.

186
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:25,730
Yes, I'm a loser.

187
00:16:25,730 --> 00:16:27,620
I got soft and came with him.

188
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:29,900
If you want to yell at me, go ahead.

189
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:35,050
We're not here to yell at you. We're happy that you can accept him.

190
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:41,550
Not that. I just want to open myself up.

191
00:16:42,252 --> 00:16:45,454
Now that you've opened up, what do you see?

192
00:16:49,810 --> 00:16:55,029
I see a version of Khai I've always wanted to see.

193
00:16:55,872 --> 00:16:58,549
The one who is not a just a friend.

194
00:17:00,075 --> 00:17:03,049
The one who feels the same way I feel.

195
00:17:24,284 --> 00:17:30,253
But when he first gets with someone, he usually does this.

196
00:17:30,253 --> 00:17:32,449
This is nothing special.

197
00:17:33,158 --> 00:17:34,769
Wait, Third.

198
00:17:34,769 --> 00:17:38,049
When did you become so jaded about love?

199
00:17:38,049 --> 00:17:44,269
P'Shane told me to use my brain more than my heart with love.

200
00:17:45,089 --> 00:17:49,607
But Khai is using his heart with you entirely.

201
00:17:49,607 --> 00:17:52,529
If you want to find out the answer,

202
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:56,229
you need to use your heart to make a decision.

203
00:18:02,763 --> 00:18:04,955
What are you guys talking about?

204
00:18:05,603 --> 00:18:07,681
Don't shush me.

205
00:18:07,681 --> 00:18:10,200
You two pay up.

206
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,497
I paid for Third only.

207
00:18:12,497 --> 00:18:15,748
Nothing you say will change my mind.

208
00:18:15,748 --> 00:18:17,170
No!

209
00:18:23,155 --> 00:18:25,275
Why are you rearranging your condo?

210
00:18:25,275 --> 00:18:27,732
You often said my room was messy.

211
00:18:27,732 --> 00:18:32,253
So, I am decluttering it so that you can come over and watch movies.

212
00:18:36,932 --> 00:18:38,974
It's good you're here.

213
00:18:38,974 --> 00:18:40,967
I've got a movie for you.

214
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,720
[Spirited Away]

215
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:46,300
"Spirited Away."

216
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:49,304
I borrowed this film from Bone a while ago.

217
00:18:49,304 --> 00:18:52,654
I liked it very much. So, I got it for you.

218
00:18:52,654 --> 00:18:55,050
You said you wanted to watch it.

219
00:18:55,859 --> 00:18:58,571
But you don't watch amination movies.

220
00:18:58,571 --> 00:19:02,167
That was before. Now I do.

221
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:11,980
[Jeab (My Girlfriend)]

222
00:19:13,536 --> 00:19:15,658
You still kept that.

223
00:19:16,136 --> 00:19:18,489
Am I your Jeab?

224
00:19:24,139 --> 00:19:30,507
Of course, it brought me to you.

225
00:19:34,210 --> 00:19:39,557
I wasn't sure at first if I was your Jeab.

226
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:46,830
But now I'm 100% sure that you're my Noi Naa.

227
00:19:56,460 --> 00:20:02,669
What happened makes it hard for me to feel the same.

228
00:20:04,432 --> 00:20:06,589
Look into my eyes.

229
00:20:15,145 --> 00:20:17,169
Look into my eyes.

230
00:20:23,496 --> 00:20:27,729
Third, can you forget what happened?

231
00:20:27,729 --> 00:20:30,527
Let the past stay in the past,

232
00:20:30,527 --> 00:20:34,557
leaving you and me in the now and the future.

233
00:21:07,646 --> 00:21:08,973
I have to go home.

234
00:21:08,973 --> 00:21:14,309
Third, what about my answer?

235
00:21:18,111 --> 00:21:21,053
You said if you finished rearranging your condo,

236
00:21:21,053 --> 00:21:23,199
you'd invite me here to watch a movie.

237
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:27,158
Let me know when you're done. We can watch this together.

238
00:21:28,930 --> 00:21:30,293
Third!

239
00:21:30,293 --> 00:21:33,140
Third! Hold on!

240
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:48,665
"Begin Again."

241
00:21:48,665 --> 00:21:52,032
Third, you'll begin again with me. Right?

242
00:21:52,032 --> 00:21:55,680
Thanks! Woohoo!

243
00:22:00,012 --> 00:22:03,092
Let's begin again.

244
00:22:03,092 --> 00:22:06,210
Third, I will not let you go ever again.

245
00:22:19,804 --> 00:22:21,410
Please wait.

246
00:22:39,032 --> 00:22:41,493
I must have been heartbroken.

247
00:22:41,493 --> 00:22:42,995
Heartbroken?

248
00:22:42,995 --> 00:22:44,592
Who?

249
00:22:45,744 --> 00:22:47,989
That person just became unavailable.

250
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:04,802
In this scene, the boy and the girl are together.

251
00:23:04,802 --> 00:23:09,307
But for a reason they agree on earlier,

252
00:23:09,307 --> 00:23:13,649
they cannot tell other people they are a couple.

253
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:50,729
The way they express it becomes hard.

254
00:23:52,435 --> 00:23:55,329
They act like everything is normal...

255
00:23:57,515 --> 00:24:00,758
even though they're in love.

256
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:16,469
But they're sometimes playful when no one is looking.

257
00:24:31,776 --> 00:24:35,757
When they're alone, they are very sweet...

258
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:41,769
if no one sees them.

259
00:24:55,668 --> 00:25:01,449
So point out this feeling and express it as much as you can.

260
00:25:03,629 --> 00:25:06,810
[Hang in there.]

261
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:09,830
Without being too obvious.

262
00:25:17,483 --> 00:25:19,652
How are these, Lynn? Beautiful?

263
00:25:20,610 --> 00:25:23,857
This one is good.

264
00:25:32,490 --> 00:25:34,050
Lynn.

265
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:47,748
Maybe it's just me, but I feel that lately

266
00:25:47,748 --> 00:25:50,950
my photos taken by you don't come out as good as they used to.

267
00:25:57,241 --> 00:26:01,370
Maybe it's me. I put on more weight.

268
00:26:01,370 --> 00:26:03,567
Look at this plump face.

